.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-9::.
4 different games are played: mah-jongg, chess, snooker, domino
There 4 different types of food: onion, eggplant, carrot, peas
1. the person playing mah-jongg is in an odd position##4
2. the person eating eggplant is not the person playing domino##6
3. the person eating onion is somewhere to the right of the person playing snooker##5
4. the person eating peas is in an even position##4
5. the person eating peas is on the left of the person eating carrot##1
6. the person eating peas is the person playing snooker##1
7. the person playing mah-jongg is not the person eating peas##6
8. the person playing chess is somewhere to the right of the person playing domino##5

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |   2    |     3      |     4     |
| Job         | mah-jongg  | snooker | domino    | chess |
| Transport   | eggplant | peas | carrot | onion  |

